¬†I had recently switched to KDE from Gnome and was looking for an Alternative for Geary. I really liked how fast Geary was and neither Thunderbird nor KMail could act as a replacement for my need(Simple and fast). Before giving up for another Electron app, I gave a try to Trojita and immediately fell in love with its speed. It was blazingly fast to the extent even Geary could never match! This is a simple guide to setup Trojita for Gmail.¬†

![](data:image/png;base64,)  

### Sources:

*   [OMG Ubuntu](httpss://www.omgubuntu.co.uk/2017/02/install-trojita-email-app-ubuntu)
*   [Google Support](httpss://support.google.com/mail/answer/185833?hl=en-GB)

### Overview:

You need to make use of _App Passwords_ in Google Account in order to access Trojita through Gmail (The other way is to enable _Less Secure App Access_ which doesn't sound inviting!). App Passwords, in turn, need _2-Factor Authentication_ turned on.

After installing Trojita, you need to setup IMAP servers for Gmail.  

1.  Turn on 2- Step Verification  
    
2.  Set up App Passwords
3.  Install Trojita
4.  Logging in with Gmail  
    

### 1\. Turn on 2-StepVerification

### ![](data:image/png;base64,)  

1.  Open your [Google Account](httpss://myaccount.google.com/).
2.  In the navigation panel, select **Security**.
3.  Under ‚ÄúSigning in to Google,‚Äù select **2-Step Verification** > **Get started**.
4.  Follow the on-screen steps.

¬†After you set up 2-Step Verification, you‚Äôll sign in to your account in two steps using:

*   Something you know, like your password
*   Something you have, like your phone (Tap Yes/No in the notification that pops up)  
    

### 2\. Setting up App Passwords

### ¬†![](data:image/png;base64,)

1.  Go to your [Google Account](httpss://myaccount.google.com/).
2.  On the left navigation panel, choose **Security**.
3.  On the 'Signing in to Google' panel, choose **App passwords**.¬†If you don‚Äôt see this option:  
    *   2-Step Verification is not set up for your account. (Note: Use your Phone to sign in != 2-Step Verification in Google ü§∑)  
        
    *   2-Step Verification is set up for security keys only
    *   Your account is through work, school or other organisation
    *   You‚Äôve turned on Advanced Protection for your account
4.  At the bottom, choose **Select app** and choose **Other**.  
    
5.  Type in '**Trojita**'.  
    
6.  Choose **Generate**.
7.  The app password¬†is the 16-character code in the yellow bar¬†on your device.

### 3\. Installing Trojita

In Ubuntu Konsole,¬†

```
sudo apt install trojita  

```

You can install the same using the respective store in your distro.  

### 4\. Logging in with Gmail Account

### ![](data:image/png;base64,)

1.  Open Trojita. If it doesn't show up settings, go to IMAP > Settings.
2.  In the General Tab, set up **Passwords** as _Secure Storage via QtKeychain_. Trojita's default stores your password as plain text (so does many other popular Email clients!)
3.  Go to IMAP tab and set up the following.

*   **Encryption**: Force Encryption (TLS)
*   **Server**: imap.gmail.com
*   **Port**: 993
*   **Username**: yourusername@gmail.com
*   **Password**: Your\_App\_Password

5.  Go to SMTP tab and set up the following.

*   **Encryption**: Force Encryption (TLS)
*   **Server**: smtp.gmail.com
*   **Port**: 465
*   Enable **Authenticate**.
*   Enable **Use IMAP Credentials.**
*   **Sent Folder Name**: \[Gmail\]/Sent Mail

7.  Click **Save**.¬†
8.  Enjoy the Lightning Speed mailing!
